HOUSE SUBSTITUTE FOR
SENATE BILL NO. 577
A bill to amend 1976 PA 399, entitled
"Safe drinking water act,"
by amending section 9 (MCL 325.1009), as amended by 2021 PA 107.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF MICHIGAN ENACT:
1 Sec. 9. (1) The department shall classify public water
2 supplies, including water treatment and distribution systems at
3 community supplies, with regard to size, type, location, and other
4 physical conditions for the purpose of establishing the skill,
5 knowledge, and experience that individuals need to maintain and
6 operate the systems effectively.
7 (2) The director shall appoint an advisory board of examiners
8 that shall assist the department in the examination of individuals
9 as to their competency to operate water treatment systems and water
RMH S04562'25 (H-1) 2ix6ey

2
1 distribution systems. The advisory board shall make recommendations
2 to the department relative to the certification of those
3 individuals.
4 (3) The membership of the advisory board consists of all of
5 the following:
6 (a) Two certified water treatment operators.
7 (b) Two certified water distribution operators.
8 (c) One superintendent or manager of a supplier of water.
9 (d) One representative of the administrative branch of a local
10 governmental agency.
11 (e) Two members of the public at large.
12 (f) One professor of sanitary or environmental engineering at
13 a university in this state.
14 (4) A representative of the department shall be the nonvoting
15 secretary for the board.
16 (5) For individuals meeting that meet the requirements, the
17 department shall issue certificates acknowledging that acknowledge
18 their competency to operate a specified class of waterworks system
19 or portion of waterworks system. The department may suspend or
20 revoke a certificate as specified by rule.
21 (6) A public water supply must be under the supervision of a
22 properly certified operator as specified in the rules promulgated
23 under this act.
24 (7) Operators certified under this act shall renew their the
25 certificates in accordance with the rules promulgated under this
26 act, including mandatory continuing education or competency
27 demonstration.
28 (8) In accordance with section 3110 of the natural resources
29 and environmental protection act, 1994 PA 451, MCL 324.3110, the
